    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/511: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 31, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Remarking that the negotiation of the new treaty would inevitably take time,
                        Torriente<note n="20" xml:id="d106fn20">Cosme de la Torriente, Cuban
                        Secretary of State.</note> has inquired whether it would be feasible for the
                    President to obtain authority to increase the Cuban preferential on sugar
                    imported into the United States in compensation for a general blanket increased
                    preferential on American imports into Cuba which could be promptly negotiated by
                    means of an exchange of notes. He states that the Cuban Provisional Government
                    has the authority to increase the American preferential.</p>
                <p>I understand, of course, that nothing of this kind could be done in any event
                    until the quota matter is disposed of.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
